    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-03T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-03T08:00:00-05:00" n="544"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d544">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1528: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-03T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 3, 1935—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 3—11:58 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>411. A communiqué has just been issued by the Secretariat giving the following
                    communication dated October 3rd to the Secretary General from the Ethiopian
                    Foreign Minister.</p>
                <pb facs="0765" n="663" xml:id="pg_663"/>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Please communicate to Council and States Members: Telegram received this
                        morning October 3rd from Ras Seyum informs Imperial Government that Italian
                        military airplanes this morning bombarded Adowa and Adigrat making numerous
                        victims among civilian population, women and children and destroying
                        numerous houses. Battle at present taking place in Province of Agame. These
                        facts occurring in Ethiopian territory constitute violation of Empire
                        frontier and breach of Covenant by Italian aggression.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
